## Source of Truth

Before ANY change, read:

1. `/docs/features/country-browser.md`
2. `/docs/features/_overview.md`

Use `Logic.md` for Countries / Recents / Profiles tab behavior.

## Reusable Components

From `/docs/features/country-browser.md` — Dependencies on Shared Code:

| Path | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `src/app/components/flagComponents.tsx` | `getFlagUrl` and flag URLs |
| `src/imports/Fastest.tsx` | Fastest row icon |
| `src/imports/svg-6mqrghog0w.ts`, `svg-gr3yl27tf4.ts`, `svg-m0k6r02h9x.ts` | Chip/tab/search SVG paths |
| `src/imports/profile-icons/*` | Profile row SVG assets |

If a shared component covers 80%+ of the requirement, extend it via props/config. Do NOT fork it. Do NOT create a parallel version.

## Feature-Specific Constraints

- Preserve `CountryRowProps` discriminated union (`vpn` vs `navigate`) type safety.
- Tab and search behavior are specified in `Logic.md` (country browser sections).

## Patterns to Follow

- Local state for `activeTab`, search, and country sub-tabs; callbacks upward for selection and VPN actions.

## What NOT to Do

- Do NOT collapse `CountryRow` variants into untyped props.
- Do NOT duplicate Figma SVG modules or `Fastest` — import from `src/imports/`.
- Do NOT modify `App.tsx` wiring without approval.
- Do NOT add routes not listed in the feature doc (none).
- Do NOT change public props of `CountryBrowser` / `CountryRow` without updating `/docs/features/country-browser.md` and parent `ISPRegulationsPanel.tsx`.
